clmn sme-dsbl-margin-left sme-dsbl-margin-right\">\n<div class=\"smue-text-obj\">\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">“Clear propagation is our ONLY responsibility”</span> [Surah Yaseen, Aayat 17]</h4>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\t\t</header><!-- .site-header -->\n\t\t<script language=\"javascript\" type=\"text/javascript\">\n\t\t\tvar cur_page_data = {pageid:\"388\", pagename:\"distractions-during-salaat\"};\n\t\t\tvar cur_themes_url = \"http://jamiat.joburg/site-data/themes\";\n\t\t</script>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"site-content\">\n\n<div id=\"primary\" class=\"content-area\">\n\t<main id=\"main\" class=\"site-main\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t\n<article id=\"post-388\" class=\"post-388 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry\">\n\t<header class=\"entry-header\">\n\t\t<h1 class=\"entry-title\">DISTRACTIONS DURING SALAAT</h1>\t</header><!-- .entry-header -->\n\n\t\n\t\n\t<div class=\"entry-content\">\n\t\t<div class=\"sm-row-fluid smue-row sme-dsbl-margin-left sme-dsbl-margin-right\">\n<div class=\"sm-span12 smue-clmn  sme-dsbl-margin-left sme-dsbl-margin-right\">\n<div class=\"smue-text-obj\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Hadhrat Aishah </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">(radhiallahu anha)</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;reports that once Nabi </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">(sallallahu alaihi wasallam)</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;was performing Salaat in a garment that had some markings (patterns) on it. Upon completion of Salaat, Nabi </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">(sallallahu alaihi wasallam)</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;said, “The patterns on this (garment) distracted me (during Salaat). Take it to Abu Jahm and bring me (in its place) an Ambijaaniyah (a plain garment).”</span></em></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"> [Saheeh Muslim / Sunan Ibn Majah]</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Hadhrat Anas </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">(radhiallahu anha)</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;reports that Nabi </span><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">(sallallahu alaihi wasallam)</span></em></strong><strong><em><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;said to him, “O my son! Save yourself from being distracted in Salaat, because indeed distraction in Salaat is destruction.”</span></em></strong><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\"> [Sunan Tirmidhi]</span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 1.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Rockwell Extra Bold',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">PLACING OF SPECTACLES DURING SALAAT</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">Many people who wear spectacles, remove them during Salaat and place them on the carpet in front of them. This is inappropriate for numerous reasons:</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- &#091;if !supportLists&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--&#091;endif&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">It causes a distraction to those close by, because inadvertently, the eyes will fall on the spectacles laying there.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- &#091;if !supportLists&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--&#091;endif&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">If a space opens up in the saff ahead (i.e. the person’s wudhu breaks and he has to leave the Musjid), then the one who has his spectacles on the carpet will not be able to move forward. This will also apply if the space next to him opens up.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- &#091;if !supportLists&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt 'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><!--&#091;endif&#093;--><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">If someone needs to exit the Musjid in a hurry whilst Jamaat is in progress, there is a fear that he may step on these spectacles laying on the ground.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Junegull; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: red;\">IT IS ADVISABLE TO EITHER KEEP THE SPECTACLES ON DURING SALAAT OR PLACE THEM IN ONE’S POCKETS.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 16.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Rockwell Extra Bold',serif; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">CELLPHONES IN THE MUSJID</span></strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.0pt; line-height: 107%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin;\">The harms of placing a cellphone on the ground in front of one during Salaat is also inappropriate for all the above reasons. The biggest distraction here will be if the phone rings, vibrates or buzzes with messages.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: Junegull; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-theme-font: minor-latin; color: red;\">IT IS STRONGLY ADVISED TO AVOID BRINGING CELLPHONES TO THE MUSJID at all. IF ONE HAS A CELLPHONE THEN IT MUST BE SWITCHED OFF TO AVOID ANY DISTRACTION IN THE HOUSE OF ALLAH TA`ALA!</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\t</div><!-- .entry-content -->\n\n\t<footer class=\"entry-footer\">\n\t\t<span class=\"byline\"><span class=\"author vcard\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2a292f79de62ec98417064d4a4611884?s=49&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g\" srcset=\"http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2a292f79de62ec98417064d4a4611884?s=98&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x\" class=\"avatar avatar-49 photo\" height=\"49\" width=\"49\"><span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Author </span> <span style=\"font-size: 15px; cursor:pointer\">ayugqoxu</span></span></span><span class=\"posted-on\"><i class=\"fa fa-calendar\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i><span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Posted on </span><a href=\"../blog/distractions-during-salaat.html\" rel=\"bookmark\"><time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2018-11-17T13:45:31+00:00\">November 17, 2018</time><time class=\"updated\" datetime=\"2018-11-17T13:56:40+00:00\">November 17, 2018</time></a></span>\t\t\t</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->\n</article><!-- #post-## -->\n\n\t<nav class=\"navigation post-navigation\" role=\"navigation\">\n\t\t<h2 class=\"screen-reader-text\">Post navigation</h2>\n\t\t<div class=\"nav-links\"><div class=\"nav-previous\"><a href=\"../blog/performing-salaat-on-a-chair.html\" rel=\"prev\"><span class=\"meta-nav\" aria-hidden=\"true\">Previous</span> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Previous post:</span> <span class=\"post-title\">PERFORMING SALAAT ON A CHAIR</span></a></div><div class=\"nav-next\"><a href=\"../blog/hifz-graduation-ceremonies.html\" rel=\"next\"><span class=\"meta-nav\" aria-hidden=\"true\">Next</span> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Next post:</span> <span class=\"post-title\">HIFZ ‘GRADUATION’ CEREMONIES</span></a></div></div>\n\t</nav>\n\t</main><!-- .site-main -->\n\n</div><!-- .content-area -->\n\n\n\t\t</div><!-- .site-content -->\n\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t<footer id=\"colophon\" class=\"site-foo